description: Wonder Woman isn’t exactly thrilled to be battling croco-aliens…but really, anything’s better than sitting through any more of that newspaper interview. And Lois Lane agrees!
name: Girls’ Day Out Part 2 of 2

description:
Miracleman's existence has been revealed in a shocking fashion! Confronted with this new reality, he chooses to take action and realize his destiny.

From the ashes of great tragedy, the world will be reborn. The sick will be healed. Military powers will be disarmed. The planet will be restored. Poverty will be abolished. Every day shall be a day of miracles...a new dawn for humankind!

The original Miracleman opus comes to its majestic close in "Olympus"!

Including material originally presented in MIRACLEMAN (1985) #16, plus bonus content.

Story Titles and Extras

  • "Olympus" from Miracleman #16, December 1989
  • Miracleman Behind the Scenes

A creative force whose pioneering efforts in the area of sound production and special affects forever changed the way we view movies, George Lucas found fame in 1977 with the release of Star Wars. Read the story behind the master filmmaker the shaped geek culture for generations.

description:
TRUCKS vs. BIKES!

Trace wakes from the bender of a lifetime to find that a cranked-out biker gang—Los Santos de la Muerte—have stolen his stolen truck . . . and his dog! What the hell? But Trace’s guardian angel may not be what she seems, and the bounty-hunting devil on his heels is catching up!

EXCLUSIVELY ON DARK HORSE DIGITAL!
name: Fate, Tx

description: Otis Pedblocker is a big, meaty hunk of naiveté and good ol' American values. When his proclivity for mindless violence brings him to the attention of the art community and Hollywood (not always the same thing), Otis discovers that there are all sorts of people out there -- most of whom he doesn't approve. Pretentious artists, snotty airlines, and smut peddlers fall before the terrible wrath of Otis Pedblocker.

See the events that spawned the predatory desert mutants of Wes Craven's The Hills Have Eyes in this adults-only graphic novel of horror from Fox Atomic, the perfect companion to the upcoming sequel to 2006's hit reimagining of the terror-filled film classic!
name: GN

The Avengers set continues with issue 22, Black Queen - Viper.

The vengeful Viper is the black-hearted Black Queen with the Marvel Chess Collection Part 22. The criminal mastermind and head of HYDRA is perfectly cast as the most powerful piece on the side of the villains.This femme fatale s tragic history that led to her leading a major terrorist organisation is explored in the magazine, with her most lethal schemes, her bizarre attachment to an octopus and the truth about her daughter .

description:
This issue consists of a hand painted figurine and a magazine on the issues featured character, The Vision.

The Avengers set continues with issue 22, White Rook - The Vision.

The Marvel Chess Collection Part 23 welcomes android Avenger, the Vision, as a heroic White Rook. Once a weapon aimed at Earth s Mightiest Heroes, the Vision is now one of the Avengers most dependable and powerful teammates.The Vision s connection to the original Human Torch, Wonder Man and the human-hating machine Ultron are revealed in the magazine, along with his incredible powers, unique romance with the Scarlet Witch and a classic cover poster.
name: The Vision [White Rook]

Inside this issue: a bad batch of booze spells undead disaster for St. Patrick's Day revellers, mankind sinks its trigger-happy teeth into intergalactic assassination, the president of earth sells his own race down the river, advances in gene-blending reveal a darker side to humanity, and Travis Wilson battles the demons of his mind in the continuation of eight part sci-fi series 'Death Duty' (all other strips are self contained).

Featuring the likes of John Freeman (Marvel UK, Judge Dredd Magazine), Val Ramon (D4VE, Outre), Chris Sides (Dark Matter, British Showcase Anthology), Dan Cornwell and more!

Burning Leaves

The Fae are revealed within Eden Park. Melody announces the presence of a truant who will hunt them all down. Meanwhile the truant pushes Kara further into becoming his weapon. She is set against Mike with disastrous consequences.
name: Burning Leaves

description: As the Joker's final gag at Arkham Asylum unfolds, one of the Batman's most dangerous enemies plots his return to Gotham City and the Arkham Knight makes an unusual discovery...
name: Death of A Rival, Part 3 of 3

description: Someone attempts to kill the injured Professor Cahn in his hospital room. But when Batman takes off after the assailant, he may be stepping into an ambush.

Menace Goes Wild!

The Menace Goes Wild as Dennis the Menace and Gnasher raise some MONSTER laughs! There's a roller coaster riot, pirate peril on the high seas... er... high street, Hallowe'en high-jinks, and some elephant-astic fun in this collection of comic capers with the wildest duo around! Menaces Unite!
name: Menace Goes Wild

volume.name: The Beano presents Dennis the Menace and Gnasher

description:
Mega Menacing!

There's Mega-Menacing Ahoy with Dennis the Menace and Gnasher! We've laughs in store when Dennis and Gnasher go shopping, they're on a roll with some wheely-good skateboard stunts, and watch out for some absolutely abominable snowmen in this collection of top comic classics! Mega-Menaces Unite!
name: Mega Menacing

volume.name: The Beano presents Dennis the Menace and Gnasher

description:
Thumbs Up For Menacing!

Thumbs Up For Menacing! That's what everyone except the softest softy will be yelling when they see Dennis the Menace and Gnasher'enjoying' a damp and dismal caravan holiday, trying out every trick in the book in the library, and scaling the heights of nonsense when a giant-sized Gnasher goes on a sausage-scented spree! Menaces Unite!
name: Thumbs Up For Menacing

volume.name: The Beano presents Dennis the Menace and Gnasher

description:
Monster Menaces!

Keep on trucking with Dennis and Gnasher, the Monster Menaces! In this collection of mad, menacing mirth, you'll meet a prehistoric pest, three guzzling grizzly bears, a rampaging robot and a zombie cop... not that they'll be much of a match for those two little monsters, Dennis the Menace and Gnasher! Monsters... er... Menaces Unite!
name: Monster Menaces

volume.name: The Beano presents Dennis the Menace and Gnasher

description: Strap yourself in for some Out of this World Menacing! Dennis and Gnasher turn from super menaces to superheroes... or do they? There's a hairy, scary surprise in the school basement in a shrieky, squeaky tale. And there's a right royal rumpus when a Very Important Person visits Beanotown. Menaces Unite!
name: Out Of This World Menacing

volume.name: The Beano presents Dennis the Menace and Gnasher

description: Are you ready for some Menacing Mayhem? Dennis and Gnasher are... and so are a galaxy of film, telly and sport stars as they join the party in Beanotown! And just like any Beanotown party, there's menacing, mischief, minxing, and... yep... mayhem on the menu! Menaces Unite!
name: Menacing Mayhem

volume.name: The Beano presents Dennis the Menace and Gnasher

description: All aboard for Menaces Making Waves! Set sail for silliness as Dennis and Gnasher tackle DIY disasters, sword and sorcery shenanigans, and a plague of zombie grown-ups! When it comes to menacing they leave everyone else all at sea! Menaces Unite!
name: Menaces Making Waves

volume.name: The Beano presents Dennis the Menace and Gnasher

description:
The Cray Origin of the Species!

The Cray-Gwash war RAGES! Our Heroes, along with the Duck and the Monkey attempt to save the hostages from the evil clutches of the Evil Gwash Monsters and their evil slime! The Battle leads to an origin of EPIC proportions! Guest starring the Cray Mayor, The Old Cray and Captain Camel and the Space Chicken! Aw Yeah First appearance! FINALLY after 20 years, the first work of ART BALTAZAR's famous cartoonist career is celebrated here for the first time! AW YEAH COMIXOLOGY! AW YEAH DIGITAL! Enjoy the Adventures!
name: The Cray Origin of the Species!

description: Serialized from the pages of Dungeon Quest Book Three by Joe Daly, we join Millenium Boy, Millenium Boy, Steve, Nerd Girl and Lash Penis mid-adventure. Having finally beaten off the Womraxes, Lash levels up with a taste of blood and all four are being watched...by the forest.
The bodies pile up and the case takes a turn for the personal, as it looks like Bigby's crime-solving partner just ended up on the wrong side of a toe tag.
name: Chapter Thirteen

description:
The age-old urban legend about an escaped, homicidal mental patient comes to life in Zenescope's newest twist on the popular tale. The fun and scary new series from the company that does horror best continues here!
